      "finding": "The Story Portal appendix names four relevant operational areas (Festival Operations, Platform Operations, Community Operations, Partner Operations) and four priorities, which shows minimal project awareness. However, none of the entries provide actionable specificity. 'Festival Operations: Event infrastructure' tells an AI agent nothing about what 'event infrastructure' means for Story Portal — is it physical venue logistics, digital streaming infrastructure, ticketing systems, creator onboarding flows? The priorities list has no metrics, no owners, no timelines, and no definition of what 'readiness' means for Priority 1. The section reads as a placeholder with Story Portal labels applied.",
      "example_rewrite": "| Area | Operational Definition | Key Metric | Current Priority | | **Festival Operations** | End-to-end readiness for live Story Portal festival events: venue coordination, creator tech setup, streaming reliability, audience access, day-of support staffing | Zero P0 incidents during festival window; creator setup completion 48h before event | 1 — Active | | **Platform Operations** | Uptime and performance of the Story Portal web/app platform supporting creator uploads, community interaction, and partner integrations | 99.5% uptime SLA; page load <2s P95; incident response <15min acknowledgment | 2 — Active | | **Community Operations** | Support infrastructure for Story Portal community: moderation tooling, creator support tickets, community health reporting | Support ticket resolution <24h; moderation queue <4h backlog | 3 — Monitoring | | **Partner Operations** | Onboarding, enablement, and SLA management for Story Portal's publisher and distribution partners | Partner onboarding cycle <14 days; SLA compliance reported monthly | 4 — Maintenance |"
